beer_description: White, smooth, compact head with a pale amber color that denotes the beer's distinctive maltiness. A rich aroma with aromatic hops, spices, and the typical fruity bouquet of a Belgian fermentable.

Thirsty Trout is a rich, robust American Porter. Dark brown in color with medium to heavy body and hints of light roast. Aromas of chocolate leave way to a full mouthfeel and somewhat sweet finish to make this porter a desirable companion..Thirsty Trout is a rich, robust American Porter that will have you yelling "CHOCOLATE!" after the first whiff. Dark brown in color with medium body and hints of light roast. The aromas of chocolate cupcake lead the way to a sweet caramel and toffee body that finish beautifully with hops. Stay trout my friends.

You will find your mouth full of flavors with every sip. First taste consists of chocolate covered raisins with subtle syrup texture leading into toffee and roasted malts. Don't expect much alcohol heat because it is poetically hidden by the creamy cocoa and espresso bean after taste at the end.
Younger?s Tartan Special is a genuine Scottish ale with a full bodied, sweet and satisfying roast flavour.
Amarillo and Cascade-hopped Belgian golden ale.

This traditional American Pale Ale is a combination of the finest Midwestern malts and American hops, creating a refreshingly crisp, citrusy, and slightly bitter taste. Named for the Greek sun god, Helios Pale Ale is a great choice for those who like a lot of personality and individuality in their beer.
Helios was given its name to reflect Upland?s commitment to environmental sustainability, specifically the installation of ten solar tube panels on the roof of the brewery, which have dramatically reduced the amount of natural gas used to heat water used in the brewing process.

- 2013 Indiana Brewers Cup Best of Show Winner
- 2013 Indiana Brewers Cup Gold Medal Winner
- 2010 World Beer Cup Silver Medal Winner
A Northwest Style IPA, a rich copper colored beer brewed with four American hop varieties producing an almost overwhelming citrus, pine and floral hop aromas.
Our pale ale, made with considerable heft from the malt bill and then complemented with classic English & American hops.
Barrel aged
Spices, cocoa nibs and ancho chile peppers.
Ethiopan lager with honey characteristics

Blood Orange Wit is a true Belgian style wheat beer brewed with Wheat, Pilsner, and German malts along with rolled oats for a palate-filling experience that will leave you feeling refreshed. Flavors and aromas of citrus, banana, and spice come from our German yeast strain, hand crushed coriander, and two types of orange peel.

Einbecker Brauherren Pils
?The Original?

A characteristic bitter taste, unique and perfectly matured.

The perfect composition of the best hops and selected fine malts bring the classic bitter character of Einbecker Brewery Premium Pils to mature perfection. The classic from Einbeck is a pure delight, either freshly tapped in a glass or in its exclusive bottle.

Ringnes Julebokk ble lansert i 1999 da loven om alkoholbegrensning p? 7 % p? ?l opphevet i Norge. I dag regnes dette ?let som en klassiker og ledestjerne blant julens mest smaksrike ?l. 

Ringnes Julebokk er en doppelbock med en dyp r?dsvart farge. Aromaen er kompleks og vin?s med noter av ristet malt, kaffe, krydder, og t?rket frukt. ?let er kraftig med en kompleks smak med mye malts?dme som balanseres godt mot en merkbar bitterhet. 

Ringnes Julebokk egner seg ogs? godt til lagring.
O?Hara?s Irish Stout has a robust roast flavour complemented by a full-bodied and smooth mouth feel.
Homebrew. AMAZING!

beer_description: Our award winning Sunlight Cream Ale infused with coffee from our friends at B. Java.
Infused with dried elderberries, currants, and rose pedals and lavender
North the Fourth was made with a 2 lb candy cane, 60 lbs of cranberries, and over 40 lbs of spruce tips. Hoppy Holidays from all of us at Fort George!
A chestnut coloured ale with a well-rounded malty aroma and a rich dried fruit flavour

As this beer is made from our Judgment Day, there are some similarities in the taste profile. However, as this beer is aged in Oak Barrels, there are also additional layers of Vanilla, Tannins and Sourness from the Cherries and the secondary fermentation and extensive aging. A massive brown ale base that is made from four fermentable sugars including Malted Barley, Raisins, Candi Sugar and Sour Cherries, this beer is fully fermented before being placed in Bourbon barrels where the beer ages for one year with the Sour Cherries and the wild Brettanomyces yeast that we inoculate the barrels with.

beer_description: Almost unhopped brown ale, undressed for the fans of the true "oud bruin" style. Aged in a 7000 l foeder. Goes by the name Undressed for USA market, goes by the name Foederbier everywhere else.
American brown ale (9% abv)

Beer styles are not always cut and dry in their definition. The Quadruple is one of those styles; loosely defined and open to more than one interpretation.  Generally speaking Quads are dark spicy Belgian ales that show their strength.  Our interpretation does not disappoint.  Sugar added to the kettle augments an already large malt bill consisting of eight different malts.  Subtle hop additions of Nugget and Czech Saaz hops contribute bitterness and a hint of spiciness that complements the alreadyspicy yeast. It all finishes off with a noticeable presence of alcohol that marries well with the spicy notes and equates into a complex brew closer in strength to wine than beer.This mahogany colored brew evokes flavors of brown sugar, apple pie, banana bread, and figs.

beer_description: Our Double Chocolate Cranberry Stout is rich and sturdy with roasted dark chocolate malts, real cocoa, 70% dark chocolate, and freshly harvested local cranberries. Pair that with a slightly higher alcohol content and you?ll find yourself sharing this bottle of joy all winter long.
beer_name: Winter Beard Double Chocolate Cranberry Stout (2011)

beer_description: You won't find an English-style brown ale quite like Muskoka Dark. Its bold colour, yet remarkably easy-going taste gives it a personality as unique as the region it's from.

A well balanced, full flavored, amber ale. It has a rich, malty body with a pleasant caramel character derived from a specialty Caravienne malt. A complex hop aroma, with a hint of floral and citrus comes from a combination of Cascades and Liberty hops. It has a rich, creamy head with a fine lace. The light fruitiness, characteristic of ales, is derived from a proprietary yeast strain. Saint Arnold Amber Ale is our flagship product and our first official brew, best consumed at 50 - 55? Fahrenheit.
Sweet potatoes and brown sugar APV 7%

A gloriously fresh imperial IPA brewed with tons of hops for a bright citrusy brew.  Light amber in color, with notes of grapefruit and tangerine zest on the nose, and a nicely balanced malt presence that's more than sweet.  Assertively hoppy, bright and balanced.
Nice orange nose but bitter orange taste.
Stout aged in whiskey and red wine barrels.

Naked Pig is a delightfully crisp, hand crafted ale. The German malts provide a perfect balance to the five hop additions that go into every batch we make. This American pale ale is tasty enough for any craft beer newcomer, while the complex character is sure to please even the most discerning craft connoisseur. So get naked and enjoy!

This traditional India Pale Ale was first produced in 1987 for a customer going through a divorce. Alimony was one of the first craft IPAs and gained cult status after articles appeared in Newsweek and Playboy. Brewed with an abundance of hops from the Pacific Northwest, 70 IBUs and 6.8% ABV. ?It?s irreconcilably different.?

By adding fresh ginger to each batch we brew, our Ginger Wheat brings a new
dimension to the American filtered wheat beer style. While still delicate and smooth,
our Wheat Beer has unique floral and citrus notes on the finish which creates a
beguiling flavor.

A contemporary rendition of a classic style, Joe's is hopped with purpose: beautifully bitter and dry with an abundance of floral, Noble German hops. Uber sessionable. Utterly American.  This is Premiuim American Pilsner.

A rock 'n roll partnership between Scotland's best new distillery (Distiller of the Year 2007) and Scotland's hardcore new microbrewery (Gold MedalWinner, World Beer Cup 2008).

Paradox, Isle of Arran Edition, see's BrewDog's killer 15% Imperial Stout matured in stunning whisky casks from the Arran distillery.

The rich vanilla sweetness, hints of cinnamon and balancing aromatic fruit and ginger flavours of the Arran Malt are all completely infused  deep into the texture of our smooth, robust, Imperial Stout.

Profund new depths emerge with each pass and sip, the pallet is as pollished and classic as a Robbie Burns masterpiece, this is Scotland in a glass.
The Ho!Ho! is a robust ?winter warmer? ale, ruby brown in color with a slightly sweet, fruity nose. Very hoppy, yet well balanced with a sturdy malt foundation.

beer_description:
Smuttynose brews Common Man Ale exclusively for the Common Man family of restaurants (http://www.thecman.com/restaurants/). 



It's only available on draft (though you might see it on tap at Smuttynose on occasion).
"A ?Real Beer' multi-malt & multi hops have made this ?Classic English Beer' another S.I.B.A. Medal Winner. Spicy & fruity, culminating in a very moreish finish. No disappointments here."
Bi?re de Garde

A rich oak-aged beer with a light hop note and strong toasty malt character. Aroma results from the seamless blend of vanilla, caramel, brandied cherry and Yakima Valley hops. Flavors of caramel and oak are offset by the warmth of alcohol. A perfect winter warmer that is well balanced to the end.

beer_description:
*** THIS IS FOR THE REGULAR VERSION ONLY. IF YOU SEE "EDITION SPECIALE" ON THE LABEL, YOU HAVE THE BARREL-AGED VERSION AND YOU SHOULD DO THE CHECK-IN UNDER EDITION SPECIALE 2015. ***

Lager noire forte inspir?e des Porters de la r?gion de la Mer Baltique.

Strong dark lager inspired from Porters found around the Baltic Sea region.
Aged in French Chardonnay barrels for 8 months, the flavors of dried fruits dance on your tongue while aromas of vanilla and oak delight your senses. 10.5 ABV, 26 IBUs
This is an Oatmeal Stout with Fidalgo Bay Roasting Co. coffee added to the finished beer. Coffee flavor and aroma blend with the dark malts in this full bodied stout.

La "9", named La Nove (Batch No. 9) for the american market, was born around the same time as La "5" in 2003. It was created with a single desire: to make a beer that they love to drink: easy to drink, with personality, recognizable without following any guidelines. Amber with orange hues that pours with a fine, compact and persistent head. It has a very ?english? aroma, with beautiful notes of candied bitter orange and caramel. The palate is very complex, consisting of the same sensations of bitter orange. A beer perfectly balanced between the sweet notes of caramel and the bitter notes in the finish. Unfiltered, unpasteurized, fermented in the bottle and keg.
Madison's finest biere de garde

This beer is brewed using spelt instead of barley. Spelt is traditionally harvested in the Duchess Mountains Regional Park. Duchessa has a golden colour with orange hues, and it is slightly hazy with a plentyful and creamy foam. It has a wide nose, fruity (banana, pineapple, tropical fruit) and floreal, with a light and pleasant peppery flavor. Carbonation is elegant, with a little sharpness and an appropriate body. It is moderately hoppy, with a pleasant and refreshing finish.
Auld Nick, which is a carefully handcrafted strong, dark ale from our Vancouver microbrewery. Once a year we skillfully blend specialty-malted grains, the traditional hops of Kent, England.

The second Christmas porter from Mikkeller. A spiced porter with fine malt background and lovely hop aroma and flavor. The label is designed as a ?From To? card ? fill in the names and put the bottle under the Christmas tree. The perfect gift for the lazy man/woman?!
Ingredients : Water, malt (pale, smoked, cara-crystal, brown and chocolate), roasted barley, dark cassonade, hops (amarillo, saaz and cascade), spices (star anise, clove, cinnamon and coriander seeds) and yeast.
beer_name: Holiday Ale From To (Til Fra via Mikkeller)

beer_description: A collaborative beer between Allagash and New Belgium brewed with the slightly fruity hibiscus flower, the aromatic Brettanomyces, and the flavor-boosting Lactobacillus.

Coppery-gold hue with a full cascade hop aroma. Rich bready malts lay a perfect foundation for the profusion of tangy, citrusy hops that infuse this beer with a distinct ruby-red grapefruit quality that starts on the palate and lingers through a long satisfying finish.
Little brother of the Baby Mastny's Imperial Stout

Springhouse is an aged Belgian Saison (Farmhouse Ale). It pours gold-amber, is will carbonated but has a small to non existent head, and has a sweet fruity aroma with apples, green grapes and apricots the dominant taste.

It?s Alive! is Mikkellers answer and tribute to the trappist beer Orval. It?s Alive is an easy-to-drink beer, with a lot of hops. The color is amber, the foam is high, white and dense. The potent Brettanomyces culture makes It?s Alive continue to develop in the bottle.
Medium-bodied and copper-colored English-style best bitter with a noticeable malt flavor. Finishes with a hop bitterness and floral hop flavor.
Wee Heavy
North the Fourth was made with a 2 lb candy cane, 60 lbs of cranberries, and over 40 lbs of spruce tips. Hoppy Holidays from all of us at Fort George!

Evoking a complete diner-style breakfast in a glass, Maple Bacon Coffee Porter is a complex beer with a multitude of flavors at play. It pours an opaque ebony brew with a frothy tan head. Aromas of sticky maple syrup, coffee, and cream creep forth from the glass. The mouth feel is luxuriously creamy, with layers of sweet malt, toffee, and roast giving way to waves of smoke, coffee, and salted chocolate. It finishes sticky, rich, and sweet, with the flavor of maple syrup lingering pleasantly on the tongue.

Winner of the World Beer CupSM 2016 Gold Medal in the Specialty Beer Category.

MBCP is available each January in bottles and draft at the brewery only as part of our Maple Bacon Coffee Porter Festival.
Dark brown/black in color with and aroma of chocolate and malt and flavors of caramel, sweet chocolate and a touch roasted barley.

The epitome of a ?farmhouse? ale, Picnic Ants is a Saison that is true to style.  Aromas of pear, citrus rind, and fresh cut grass spiral thru earthy spice into a soft, light bodied beer that tastes of tart citrus fruit and peppered orange zest. Delightfully complex with an extremely dry finish, this is a summer thirst quencher for sure. We?ve said it before and we?ll say it again.  This is the real Belgian (style) deal!
*This beer is intentionally ?funked? with brettanomyces.  Expect bottled product to develop complexity as this beer ages.

You aren't seeing things. Yes, this is a dancer ridin' a white tiger through the flooded streets of Las Vegas. No this hasn't happened. Or has it? trust us, its Possible. Enjoy the Monsoon while it last. FYI, for all of you Hop-Heads out there: Hopped with Tim Etter?s home grown Mt. Hood and Cascade

A nice golden color with aromas of pine, citrus, and some earthy spice notes. Created using only English Pale malts and seven varieties of hops! Full of hop flavors at about 100IBU?s. This is what hop lovers dream of.
Dark Island Reserve is a strong and full Orcadian Ale - lagered for 3 month in old Dalmore whiskey oakbarrals. This slow proscess makes a classic - a fruity, spiced, oakroasted maltflavour.
